==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ioqua shell
<hw>I"o*qua shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From the native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The shell of a large Dentalium (<spn>Dentalium
pretiosum</spn>), formerly used as shell money, and for ornaments, by
the Indians of the west coast of North America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iota</ent>⟦br⟧
